              "displayName": "Daniel Templeton",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Thanks for the ideas, [~zhengchenyu].  Some of what you're discussing may fall under the umbrella of YARN-5139, which is attempting to make scheduling more efficient by scheduling independent of node heartbeats.  The rest of what you're suggesting sounds like a new scheduler implementation rather than an improvement to fair scheduler.  If you consider the application and queue priority last, how can the scheduler ensure fair distribution of resources according to shares?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=templedf",
              "name": "templedf",
              "key": "templedf",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=templedf&avatarId=24879",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=templedf&avatarId=24879",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=templedf&avatarId=24879",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=templedf&avatarId=24879"
              },
              "displayName": "Daniel Templeton",
